# Basic SQL & the catalog API

## Standard ANSI query surface

- `SELECT`, `WHERE`, `GROUP BY`, `HAVING`, `ORDER BY`, `LIMIT`
- Spark SQL **supports `HAVING`** — even though DataFrames have no `.having()` (use `.filter()` after `.agg()`)

## `spark.catalog` — inspect the metastore

- **`listDatabases()`** / **`listTables()`** / **`listColumns(table)`**
- **`tableExists(name)`** — boolean guard
- **`dropTempView`** / **`dropGlobalTempView`** — cleanup

Queries read the **data**; the catalog reads the **metadata about** the data.
